A 36-year-old man, Ayo Adeleke, yesterday appeared at an Ebute Meta Magistratesâ€™ Court, Lagos, for allegedly defrauding an Uber driver of N47, 000. Adeleke, whose address was not provided, is charged with fraud, obtaining under false pretences and theft. Prosecuting counsel Maria Dauda alleged that the defendant committed the offence last November 19 at 8:40am, on Funsho Williams/Marina Way, Lagos. She said the defendant told the complainant, Mutiu Kareem, to transport him to Lekki and asked for a loan of N47, 000, which he promised to pay back when they get to their destination. When they got to Lekki, she said the defendant refused to pay the money or pay his fare. She said the defendant also stole two phones valued at N110,000 from the complainant. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Mrs. A. Kusanu granted the defendant N20,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She adjourned till June 25.